AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Fiscal Calendar Name
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Name of your new fiscal calendar when you run configuration wizard.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Name of your new fiscal calendar when you run configuration wizard.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Balance Sheet Name
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Name of new created balance sheet.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When you create balance sheet option enable, you should provide balance sheet name in this field.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Import Product Cost
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Import Product Cost to define the latest costing at the begining of accounting period
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Import Product Cost to define the latest costing at the begining of accounting period. By providing the product cost you are allowed to see the valued stock value, and also post the 1st Goods Receipt document. Beside that, you will get matched value of your inventory in the warehouse and in your balance sheet.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Create Default Accounting Period
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Create Default Accounting Period when you run configuration wizard
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: No accouting period provided. By enabling this option, you will get default accounting period. For example, if initial opening balance is 01-01-2011, its mean current year is 2011, then default period is 12 records, starting from 01-01-2011 until 31-12-2011, 1 record for each month.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Create Fiscal Calendar
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Cretae fiscal calendar when you run configuration wizard.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Cretae fiscal calendar when you run configuration wizard.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Action for Orders
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Next action taken for order transaction
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Next action taken for order transaction. Order transaction including purchase order, sales order, vendor return, customer return, and quotation.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Activate All Transaction Document
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Not all transaction activated by default, by enable this option, all inactive transaction document will be activated.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Not all transaction activated by default, by enable this option, all inactive transaction document will be activated.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Create Opening Balance Accounting Period
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Create Opening Balance Accounting Period when you run configuration wizard.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Usually, Opening balance happen before the 1st date of your accounting data live in the Openbravo. For example, when your accounting data inside openbravo is starting from 01-01-2011, then your Opening Balance, should stated as per date 31-12-2010. By enabling this option, you will get a new dedicated accounting period for opening balance, according to the case study, this period will valid only on 31-12-2010.

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Name of created warehouse when you run configuration wizard,

AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Import product price
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Import product price record, you may import prices for a product, after import its definition (and also product purchasing data, using Import Product window).

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When accounting period created, its not defined wheter the period is opened or closed. By enabling this option, you will get your default accounting period opened.

AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Used Qty for actual cost. If used qty equal to Qty, its mean all available item already used and this cost should not be used anymore.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Import Business Partner Balance

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Import business partner balance, to enable you register the payment from/lto your business partner after opening balance. You may not enter the detail of invoice, but you define how much and when you need to receive/pay to your business partner. One business partner can have several due date and amount to be received/paid.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Upon Document Routing Executed
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Determine how Openbravo handle document routing execution.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Document routing enable Openbravo user to create complex approval flow process for certain document. However, this feature requires lot of configuration. If you select "Always use document routing rule", and you don't configure the document routing rule inside role definition yet, then you can't complete the document. Selecting "Apply standard rule if no document rule defined", allow openbravo to bring standard document approval rule when you don't have any document routing configuration for selected document.
